<task id="021" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-13 Build Generic `invoke_playbook` Chat Tool (Pillar 3)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>022</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, chat</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>New chat-tool handler using PublicContracts facade; ADR-013 + ADR-015 binding; touches authorization (tenant playbook visibility); tags `bff-api`+`ai`+`chat`.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent file; gates 022 and 023.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the generic `invoke_playbook(playbookId, parameters)` chat tool as an
    `IToolHandler` implementation. The handler calls `IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync`
    (task 020) — preserving the ADR-013 facade boundary by never injecting the
    orchestration service directly. The handler validates `playbookId` against
    `sprk_analysisplaybook` rows accessible to the tenant + validates parameters against
    the playbook's parameter schema before dispatching.

    Critical-path context: this generic tool replaces the specialized
    `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` + `InvokeInsightsQueryTool` bridges (removed in task 023).
    Task 022 dynamically lists the active playbooks in the tool's description.

    Tool registration: seed a `sprk_analysistool` row with name "invoke_playbook",
    `AvailableInContexts = Chat`, valid `JsonSchema` (parameters: `playbookId: string`,
    `parameters: object`). The handler binds via the standard chat-tool resolution path
    established in task 011.

    Insights playbook-vs-RAG routing: per FR-24, the `InsightsIntentClassifier` continues
    to handle that routing internally — the generic tool dispatches to whichever execution
    path the playbook's metadata indicates.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with `IToolHandler` + chat-tool + playbook orchestration experience.
    Familiar with tenant-scoped playbook visibility + `InsightsIntentClassifier`.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `InvokePlaybookHandler : IToolHandler` exists. `sprk_analysistool` row seeded.
    Handler validates playbookId + parameters, dispatches via `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade.
    Unit tests cover happy path + validation failures + tenant-isolation enforcement.
    Build green; publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="facade">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IInvokePlaybookAi.cs</file>
    <file purpose="interface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IToolHandler.cs</file>
    <file purpose="insights-routing-guide">docs/guides/INSIGHTS-PLAYBOOK-VS-RAG-DECISION-TREE.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Register handler inside existing module; no new Program.cs lines.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Handler uses `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade ONLY; never injects `IPlaybookOrchestrationService` or other AI internals directly. Facade boundary preserved.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Cache playbook-visibility lookups per `tenantId`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry: tool name + playbookId + decision + timestamp; no parameters content; no user message text.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">No new feature flags.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Verify BFF publish-size delta; ≤+5 MB R6 budget.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-14">Tenant SYS-/CUST- enforcement on playbookId resolution.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-22">Handler validates `playbookId` against `sprk_analysisplaybook` rows accessible to tenant; validates parameters against playbook's parameter schema.</constraint>
  </constraints>

