  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — chat-tool handler + ADR-013 facade discipline".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 020 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Capture baseline publish size.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement `InvokePlaybookHandler`">
      `IToolHandler` impl injecting `IInvokePlaybookAi` (facade) + `ITenantPlaybookVisibilityService` (or equivalent). Validate playbookId against tenant-accessible rows; validate parameters against playbook's parameter schema; dispatch via facade.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Seed `sprk_analysistool` Row">
      Add row: name="invoke_playbook", AvailableInContexts=Chat, description="Invoke any registered playbook by ID with parameters. Use this when the user requests an analysis already configured as a playbook.", JsonSchema={playbookId: string, parameters: object}. Handler-class binding to the new handler. Idempotent seed script.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Register Handler in DI Module">
      Add to `AnalysisServicesModule`. No new Program.cs lines.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="🛑 Confirmation Gate — Data Seed Deployment">
      PAUSE for confirmation before seeding `sprk_analysistool` row to production Dataverse.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Deploy Row + Verify">
      Deploy via `dataverse-deploy`. Verify row visible; verify factory query (task 011) includes the new tool.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Add Unit + Integration Tests">
      Tests: happy path (valid playbookId, valid params → dispatched); validation failures (invalid id, schema mismatch); tenant isolation (cross-tenant id rejected); telemetry payload ADR-015-compliant.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Build + Verify Publish Size + Acceptance Criteria">
      `dotnet build` → 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release` → delta vs baseline. Walk each criterion.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify ADR-010 / ADR-013 / ADR-014 / ADR-015 / ADR-018 / ADR-029 + FR-22 + NFR-14 compliance. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 021 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
